Welcome! We would love to chat with you about what you are up to and introduce you to some more of the work we are doing with pillar!
And we want you to use it as you would any other app, so there will be no timeframe. And of course you can stop using it/opt out at any time!

Everything will be done remotely, we will send a survey with some questions as well as invite you to a private FB group (if you decide to opt in) to share your experiences - we understand how precious your time is so we don't want to take too much of it!
Great. What does being a tester involve? Use it once and tell you what I think or attend feedback workshops or fill in surveys... I ask because I'm trying to understand what you're asking me to do
We are interested in testing the connections in context and getting honest feedback on the UX & type of support you receive from the other mums so that we can make pillar a better service!

Using a mentor model means double the benefit. On the one hand, mums are able to gain relevant advice from mums who have been through similar situations but also we empower mums to talk about their experiences with mums one step behind in the journey.

Of course! pillar combines the power of peer-to-peer support with a unique connection system that links mums using multiple data points to ensure more relevant connections and consequently more relevant advice and support.
Can you tell me what’s involved before I sign up? Thanks x
Amazing If you sign-up here ( http://www. ourpillar.com/sign-up ) you will receive an email with some more info! Thank you!
Sure! send me details of what it involves and I’ll have a look
